***Organization Overview:***
Fictional company named PayLink Digital Solutions, founded in 2015, is a global fintech company the provide several types of products and services to its customers. It provides secure digital payment and open banking solutions for consumers, merchants and financial institutions. PayLink Dig. Sol. is headquartered in London, the company also operates across Europe, Asia and North America. The company offers products such as digital wallets, payment gateways, open banking APIs, blockchain based settlement systems and AI driven fraud detection tools. The services provided by them support industries including banking, e-commerce, insurance and SME payment platforms. The goal is to simplify global financial transactions through secure and compliant technology.



Key Deliverables: The project include the following deliverables: • ISMS Scope Document • Asset Inventory Spreadsheet • Risk Register Spreadsheet • Risk Register Documentation

Technologies Referenced in the Environment: The simulated environment includes several enterprise technologies used in modern fintech infrastructures: • Temenos T24 (core banking platform) • Salesforce Financial Cloud (CRM) • AWS SageMaker (AI fraud analytics) • Snowflake (data analytics platform) • Kubernetes and Terraform (cloud infrastructure management) • GitLab CI/CD (DevOps pipeline) • ServiceNow (IT service management)
